{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KcoyTVMiBKDLPXpgEhr3gk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the test is returning `\"Smażona zielona fasolka + Smażona zielona fasolka DLA & OSOB\"` instead of `\"Smażona zielona fasolka\"`.\n\nSo now the regex fix worked (Smażona is no longer falsely detected as a cooking instruction), but the issue is something else - there's a spurious candidate \"Smażona zielona fasolka DLA & OSOB\" that's being joined to the title.\n\nThe test text is:\n```\nSmażona zielona fasolka\nDLA & OSOB\n200g fasolki\n\n\n1 cebula\n```\n\nThe comment says: \"DLA & OSOB\" is OCR-corrupted Polish \"DLA 4 OSÓB\" (for 4 people) — metadata, not a title. The expanded DLA pattern should be filtering out \"DLA & OSOB\", but it's not catching this variant with the ampersand. I need to check if the DLA pattern in the code is broad enough to handle this corruption, or if the multi-line title merger is combining lines before the filtering happens.\n\nActually, I think I see what's going on. Before my regex fix, \"Smażona\" was incorrectly flagged as a cooking instruction due to the buggy word boundary handling with Polish characters, so the title wasn't being returned at all. Now that the regex is fixed, \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" correctly passes through, but it's getting merged with \"DLA & OSOB\" into a single spurious candidate because the DLA filtering isn't catching this corrupted variant. The test was masking a pre-existing issue — it was broken before, just in a different way.\n\nNow I need to figure out why \"DLA & OSOB\" isn't being filtered out as serving-size text and what's causing it to merge with the title.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4086,"cache_read_input_tokens":29610,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4086},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":