{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CXrsjiMWYmHsjm4MwRbtAx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 37 tests pass. Quick self-review of the three changes:\n\n1. **`looksLikeCookingInstruction`** — Polish regex checked first with 2-word threshold; English path unchanged at 4+ words. Clean and correct.\n\n2. **`POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` regex** — Replaced `\\b` with `(?![a-zA-ZąćęłńóśźżĄĆĘŁŃÓŚŹŻ])`. This was a real bug: JS `\\b` doesn't treat Polish chars as word chars, so `smaż\\b` incorrectly matched \"Smażona\". The lookahead correctly rejects any letter following the verb stem, including Polish letters. The fix preserves the behavior for all ASCII-ending alternatives (like `ugotuj`).\n\n3. **2-line/3-line join metadata guard** — Added `!looksLikeMetadata(nextLine)` before creating joins. This prevents \"Title + DLA & OSOB\" spurious candidates. Consistent: both 2-line and 3-line joins are guarded. Won't affect legitimate multi-line titles since recipe titles don't contain serving-size metadata as a middle line.\n\nNo unnecessary changes; all three fixes are tightly scoped to the task."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1187,"cache_read_input_tokens":44569,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1187},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4407852d-7747-4d05-8f35-a479d23762b1","uuid":"9211f376-739f-4636-8377-f0ad5940e55e"}
